explanation: The solution works by counting the frequency of each character in the string, then determining the number of characters with odd counts. A string can be constructed into k palindromes if and only if the number of characters with odd counts is less than or equal to k and k is less than or equal to the length of the string. This approach takes advantage of the fact that a palindrome can have at most one character with an odd count.

